# DHBW CAS - Labor IT Sicherheit - Runde 1

## Project Context

- University project: 3 weeks, 2 people
- Module: Labor IT Sicherheit (IT Security Lab)
- Focus: IT security best practices and threat mitigation
- Host: alma1.schach.kids (Alma Linux 9.6 VM)
- User: bohnenkopf (rootless, SSH key authentication)
- Local testing: Windows 11 with Docker
- Deployment: SSH → clone repo → `podman compose up -d`

## Tech Stack

- Docker Compose / Podman Compose
- nginx (reverse proxy)
- WordPress (PHP 8.4-FPM)
- MariaDB 12.0.2
- Certbot (Let's Encrypt SSL certificates)

## Security Priorities

Follow security best practices proportional to the use case described in the Notion task "Aufgabe - Runde 1". Key areas:

- SSH hardening (fail2ban, key-based auth)
- Firewall configuration (iptables/firewalld)
- Rate limiting (DoS protection)
- Path traversal protection
- AppArmor/SELinux
- XSS prevention
- Database security
- SSL/TLS configuration
- Network segmentation (internal networks)
- Container security (least privilege, read-only volumes where possible)

## Code Style

- Use standard formatting and linting for all file types
- Follow Docker Compose best practices
- Use clear, descriptive names
- Comment security-critical configurations

## Files & Structure

- Keep sensitive data out of version control (use .env files)
- Document security decisions and threat mitigations
- Maintain clear separation between dev and production configs

## Deployment Notes

- Production: Alma Linux 9.6 VM with Podman
- Local: Windows 11 with Docker
- Use `podman compose` on the VM, `docker compose` locally
